// Section 5: Deployment Topology
---

<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
  <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Section 5: Deployment Topology</h2>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Infrastructure Overview</h3>
  <p class="mb-4 text-white/70">
    The platform uses a hybrid deployment model with control plane services running in Kubernetes
    and agents deployed on customer-managed hardware.
  </p>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Control Plane (Kubernetes)</h3>
  <div class="mb-6 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-4">
    <p class="mb-2 font-semibold">Hosted on Talos Linux Kubernetes cluster:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-white/70">
      <li>- All microservices containerized</li>
      <li>- PostgreSQL databases (one per service)</li>
      <li>- RabbitMQ message broker</li>
      <li>- Redis for caching/sessions</li>
      <li>- YARP Gateway as single entry point</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Edge Layer</h3>
  <table class="mb-6 w-full border-collapse text-sm">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th class="border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-2.5 py-2 text-left text-white/90"
          >Component</th
        >
        <th class="border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-2.5 py-2 text-left text-white/90"
          >Provider</th
        >
        <th class="border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-2.5 py-2 text-left text-white/90"
          >Purpose</th
        >
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr
        ><td class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">WAF/DDoS</td><td
          class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">Cloudflare</td
        ><td class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">Protection at edge</td></tr
      >
      <tr
        ><td class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">CDN</td><td
          class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">Cloudflare</td
        ><td class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">Static asset delivery</td></tr
      >
      <tr
        ><td class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">DNS</td><td
          class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">Cloudflare</td
        ><td class="border border-white/10 px-2.5 py-2 align-top">DNS management</td></tr
      >
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Agent Deployment</h3>
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-indigo-500/35 bg-indigo-500/[0.12] p-4">
    Agents run on customer hardware (colo, cloud VMs, on-premises) and connect outbound to the
    control plane. No inbound firewall rules required on customer side.
  </div>
</div>
